19/12/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia – The Macedonian Parliament voted Friday (17 December) to elect Vlado Buckovski, 42, as the country’s new prime minister -- replacing Hari Kostov, who resigned last month. In his address to parliament, Buckovski said the country must put an end to ethnic divisions and focus on improving the economy. He promised to launch negotiations for membership in the EU and NATO in 2006. 
In other news, opposition ethnic Albanian leader Arben Xhaferi announced Friday that a deal has been made to disarm militants in the Skopje suburb of Kondovo after a standoff that lasted more than a month. President Branko Crvenkovski said the armed men had come from Kosovo and must be arrested upon their return there. (Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 18/12/04; Makfax, A1 TV, Macedonian Government Web site - 17/12/04) 
